 of Yiddish and its culture.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aYiddish languagexGrammar. 0aYiddish languagexHistory. 4aDISCOUNT-A. 7aFOREIGN LANGUAGE STUDY / Yiddish.2bisacsh1 aBaumgarten, Jean, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBaumgarten, Jean.1 aBirnbaum, David .1 aBirnbaum, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBirnbaum, Eleazar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBirnbaum, Eleazar.1 aWeiser, Kalman, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWeiser, Kalman.40uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144266533040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442665330423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442665330.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK